<img src="http://www.dur.ac.uk/butler.jcr/application/views/involved/img/upload/021.jpg" style="margin-top: 10px; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: auto; display: block; ">Welcome to Josephine Butler Gaming Society, a group to unite all Butler gamers, from casual to hardcore, whether you prefer shooting terrorists on Call of Duty, racing in Mario Kart, winning the champions league on FIFA or rocking away on Guitar Hero.<div><br /></div><div>Our aim is to link up anyone in college who fancies a bit of gaming with another like-minded Butlerite, whether it be in a flat, the JCR, the bar or online.</div><div><br /></div><div>We'll be holding weekly sessions (usually Sunday afternoon/evening) in the JCR where we can use the college's Xbox 360 and Wii consoles to play a variety of games, and<span style="line-height: 1.231;">&nbsp;want to set up tournaments once or twice a term with prizes to be won!&nbsp;</span><span style="line-height: 1.231;">With the next generation of consoles arriving just before Christmas, we're also hoping to get our hands on either the PS4 or Xbox One for the college.<br /><br />Join the facebook group (</span><a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/jbgs.group/" style="line-height: 1.231;">https://www.facebook.com/groups/jbgs.group/</a>) and don't hesitate to get in touch with me using the contact button below.<br /><br />Bill Wright</div><div><span style="line-height: 1.231;"><br /></span></div><div><div><img src="http://www.dur.ac.uk/butler.jcr/application/views/involved/img/upload/019.jpg">&nbsp;</div></div>